  "title": "Probability Decision-making Task with ambiguity",
  "description": "This dataset comprises multimodal neuroimaging and electrophysiological recordings from 53 healthy volunteers (aged 18-31 years) performing a probability decision-making task under conditions of risk and ambiguity. Data include structural MRI (T1w, T2w, DWI), task-based fMRI, and concurrent EEG recordings during transcranial magnetic stimulation applied over parietal regions and the vertex. The dataset enables investigation of neural mechanisms underlying decision-making under uncertainty, with particular focus on parietal cortex function and its interactions with distributed brain networks.",
  "methods_description": "Participants performed a probability decision-making task during fMRI acquisition. Concurrent EEG recordings were obtained during transcranial magnetic stimulation (TMS) applied over two parietal regions and the vertex. Structural MRI included T1-weighted, T2-weighted, and diffusion-weighted imaging sequences.",
